snapshot.body:
Implement a mistune renderer that emits ADF for block-level nodes:
- paragraph → {type: paragraph, content: [...]}
- heading (1-6) → {type: heading, attrs: {level: N}, content: [...]}
- code block → {type: codeBlock, attrs: {language: X}, content: [{type: text, text: ...}]}
- blockquote → {type: blockquote, content: [paragraph nodes]}
- thematic break → {type: rule}

Create src/jira/adf.py with the renderer. TDD each node type.

Done when: each block node converts correctly with tests.

Extend the ADF renderer to handle lists:
- bullet list (- item) → {type: bulletList, content: [listItem nodes]}
- ordered list (1. item) → {type: orderedList, content: [listItem nodes]}
- listItem → {type: listItem, content: [paragraph or nested list]}

Nested lists should work (list inside list item).

Done when: flat and nested lists convert correctly with tests.

